OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise for Power NI and
OL,4,CFirmus customers
OL,6,FEnergy prices are set to rise in
OL,7,FNorthern Ireland from July 1, the
OL,8,FUtility Regulator has confirmed.
OL,10,FOn Friday 29 May, it was announced
OL,11,Fthat Power NI's electricity unit price
OL,12,Fwill increase by 6.2%, representing an
OL,13,Fincrease of around #5 per month for
OL,14,Fthe average household.
OL,16,FFirmus' natural gas tariff will rise
OL,17,Fby 15.65% for its Ten Towns customers,
OL,18,Fwhich equates to an additional #10.70
OL,19,Fa month for the average household.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/10
