OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise for Power NI and
OL,4,CFirmus customers
OL,6,FWilliam Steele, from Power NI, said:
OL,7,F"This tariff adjustment is not a
OL,8,Fdecision we've taken lightly.
OL,10,F"We have worked hard to hold prices
OL,11,Ffor as long as possible, but sustained
OL,12,Fincreases in global gas costs, along
OL,13,Fwith higher network and market related
OL,14,Fcharges, means unfortunately this
OL,15,Fincrease is unavoidable."
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,442,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F441A1780085152
OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise for Power NI and
OL,4,CFirmus customers
OL,6,F"We know this is unwelcome, however,
OL,7,Fwe've delayed the change as long as we
OL,8,Fcould, while keeping our tariffs
OL,9,Fcompetitive locally and below the
OL,10,Faverage in GB and the Republic of
OL,11,FIreland."
OL,13,FDavid Smith, from Firmus Energy said:
OL,14,F"Over recent months we have been
OL,15,Fmonitoring global markets closely and
OL,16,Fprotecting consumers from price
OL,17,Fchanges for as long as possible.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@IO]vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
